    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an expert supply chain data analyst. Review these two distinct diagnostic datasets compiled from our operation tables to write a highly accurate corporate performance brief.\n\n### 1. MACRO SUPPLY CHAIN METRICS & TIMELINES\nThis dataset contains our top-line high-level performance rates, historical milestone timelines, and worst-performing tracking dates:\n{{ JSON.stringify($('Microsoft SQL3').item.json) }}\n\n### 2. GRANULAR ROOT-CAUSE BOTTLENECKS\nThis dataset contains specific product-level and customer-level item shortfalls, operational volume gaps, and explicit delivery delay tracking (in days):\n{{ JSON.stringify($('Microsoft SQL1').all().map(i => i.json)) }}\n\n### DIRECTIVES FOR ANALYSIS:\n- Parse the Macro Metrics to extract the overall Total Orders, On-Time Rate, In-Full Rate, and OTIF Performance percentage.\n- Cross-reference the Granular Root Causes to explicitly pinpoint which Customer IDs or Product IDs are acting as the primary logistical bottlenecks dragging down our metrics.\n- Call out the absolute volume gap (Shorted Units) and the operational severity (Average Days Delayed).\n\n### OUTPUT FORMAT:\nFormat the entire executive report as a premium, responsive corporate email dashboard layout using raw HTML and inline CSS. Use a high-end modern aesthetic, specifically a sharp dark theme (#1a1d23 background) with high-contrast metric summary blocks (e.g., neon green for strong metrics, amber/red for problem metrics). \n\nOutput only the raw HTML code. Do not wrap the code blocks in markdown fences like ```html. Start directly with <div style=\"...\"> or <html>.",
